io.nats.client

Class Options

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.nats.client.Options

  • public class Options
extends Object
    An Options object contains the immutable (and some mutable) configuration settings for a Connection.

    The Options object is constructed using methods of an Options.Builder as in the following example: 

        Options opts = new Options.Builder()
            .noReconnect()
            .timeout(3, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
            .build();

    // Now connect
    Connection nc = Nats.connect("nats://example.company.com:4222", opts);
